values.Script: Dialogue(Mother Nature created us. She can destroy us too!)

Set(StillShopping, true)
While(StillShopping == true)
   Choice(Show Food Money, Buy Food $1, Stay the Night $5, No Thanks)
      Case BuyFood
         If(Money < 1)
            Dialogue(What do you take me for!?)
            Set(StillShopping, false)
         If(Money >= 1)
            Incr(FoodSupply, 1)
            Incr(Money, -1)
      Case Stay The Night
         If(Money < 5)
            Dialogue(What do you take me for!?)
         If(Money >= 5)
            Incr(Money, -5)
            Inn()
            DayPass(WorldMap, 97, 58)
         Set(StillShopping, false)
      Case NoThanks
         Set(StillShopping, false)

Choice(Show Food Money Days, Continue Exploring, End The Day)
   Case Continue Exploring
      Move(Player, Up 1)
   Case End The Day
      DayPass(WorldMap, 97, 58)

If(Party != AnyoneDead)
   Dialogue(This is the hospital.)
   Dialogue(If you're out and about and someone is seriously hurt - don't take your chances.)
   Dialogue(Come by if anyone ever loses all of their [Hearts]. We'll patch them up for $15.)
If(Party == AnyoneDead)
   Choice(Show Money, Admit KOd Members $15, No Thanks)
      Case Admit KOd Members
         If(Money < 15)
            Dialogue(You don't have enough money.)
         If(Money >= 15)
            HealDead()
            Incr(Money, -15)
            FadeOut()
            FadeIn()
            Dialogue(Your KOd Members were brought back.)
      Case No Thanks
         Wait(0.1)

Choice(Show Food Money Days, Continue Exploring, End The Day)
   Case Continue Exploring
      Move(Player, Up 1)
   Case End The Day
      DayPass(WorldMap, 97, 58)

Choice(Show Food Money Days, Continue Exploring, End The Day)
   Case Continue Exploring
      Move(Player, Up 1)
   Case End The Day
      DayPass(WorldMap, 97, 58)

Choice(Show Food Money Days, Continue Exploring, End The Day)
   Case Continue Exploring
      Move(Player, Up 1)
   Case End The Day
      DayPass(WorldMap, 97, 58)
Dialogue("All of our children should strive to be like DirtDawg. So loyal.")

values.Name: King
values.Script: Dialogue(Destroy the leader of the wicked nation!)

Dialogue(It's DirtDawg we have to thank for peace in our country.)
Dialogue(He's the one who trained all of us soldiers.)
Dialogue(I'm glad we have an army to protect us from the Wicked Nation.)

Dialogue(King: So you're a hero huh? You'll have to prove it.)
Dialogue(King: There is a wicked nation to the north.)
Move(DirtDawg, Down 1)
Dialogue(DirtDawg: Their existence threatens the glory of Capricorn.)
Move(DirtDawg, Up 1)
Face(DirtDawg, Down)
Dialogue(King: We're launching an all-out assault on the Wicked Nation.)
Dialogue(King: All of our loyal soldiers are going.)
Face(King, Right)
Dialogue(King: DirtDawg is the loyalest of all.)
Face(King, Down)
Dialogue(King: He will accompany you.)
Move(DirtDawg, Down 2)
Face(King, Down)
Erase(DirtDawg)
Dialogue(DirtDawg joined the party!)
AddPartyMember(DirtDawg)
Set(DirtDawgJoined, true)
Dialogue(King: The wicked nation has shacked up inside a cave to the north.)
Dialogue(King: Together you will infiltrate it and assassinate their leader.)
Dialogue(King: Go now DirtDawg! Remember your training! Prove your loyalty!)
Dialogue(DirtDawg taught me what it means to be loyal!)
